The National Hajj Commission of Nigeria (NAHCON) said it has taken the cancellation of international pilgrimage for 2020 Hajj in good faith, stressing that it was the will of Allah and commended the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia for the brave decision. The commission in a statement issued by the head of Public Affairs, Fatima Sanda Usara, acknowledged the outpouring of interests and enquiries by individuals, pressmen and other stakeholders over the  cancellation. It assured Nigerians that it will fulfill all administrative, cum official requirements concerning the cancellation, saying the chairman and CEO of the commission will hold a press briefing where all your enquiries and way forward will be addressed. “The Commission’s leadership, board members and management welcome the news with complete surrender to the will of the Almighty, and commend the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia for this brave decision. “NAHCON is sensitive to all the enquiries and concerns that greeted Saudi Arabia’s much awaited decision. Hence, the Commission assures the general public that as soon as its leadership fulfills all administrative, cum official requirements, the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of NAHCON shall hold a press briefing where all your enquiries and way forward will be addressed,” the commission said. The commission however urged intending pilgrims to remain calm as necessary arrangements are in place to protect their interest, saying it appreciates the prayers and support extended to it from all  segments of the society. 